main event: Multiple civilian witnesses reported seeing a round, white and green glowing object over Las Vegas, Nevada on March 11, 1965.
interesting points: The object was described as round in shape, with white and green lights that were very bright.
The object moved north, faded out, and disappeared in a northeasterly direction.
Other witnesses reported seeing the object at different times, suggesting they were observing the same object.
The witnesses included a high school student, a TV station public relations clerk, and a bartender, though their reliability was noted to be variable.
The object was observed for periods ranging from less than a minute to an hour and a half.
sighted object: round, white and green glowing object
